{"word":"θέλημα","slug":"θέλημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϑέλημα, ατος, τό</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θέλω\">θέλω</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘that which is to be carried out according to wish or purpose’, <b>will <a href='B:470 6:10'>Mt 6:10</a>; <a href='B:490 12:47'>Lk 12:47</a>; <a href='B:500 6:38-40'>J 6:38-40</a>; <a href='B:510 21:14'>Ac 21:14</a>; <a href='B:520 2:18'>Ro 2:18</a>; <a href='B:520 12:2'>12:2</a>; <a href='B:560 1:9'>Eph 1:9</a>; <a href='B:620 2:26'>2 Ti 2:26</a>; <a href='B:650 10:10'>Hb 10:10</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘act of willing’ <b>will, desire <a href='B:490 23:25'>Lk 23:25</a>; <a href='B:500 1:13'>J 1:13</a>; <a href='B:520 15:32'>Ro 15:32</a>; <a href='B:530 7:37'>1 Cor 7:37</a>; <a href='B:550 1:4'>Gal 1:4</a>; <a href='B:670 3:17'>1 Pt 3:17</a>; <a href='B:680 1:21'>2 Pt 1:21</a>; <a href='B:690 5:14'>1 J 5:14</a>.</b> <el>τὰ ϑελήματα τῆς σαρϰὸς</el> things desired by the old self <b><a href='B:560 2:3'>Eph 2:3</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Θέκλα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:θέλησις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}